commit.message:
pull: resolve the image config and set it on stored image (#326)

Previously `pull` would not properly retain the image configuration
which contains the entrypoint, working directory, user, and more. This
resulted in broken images if they were pulled then subsequently pushed.

This commit fetches the image config, which must be done separately, and
then ensures that the configuration is set on the exported image into
the local img state store.

commit.message:
`img inspect` command: dump the JSON for the image config to stdout (#324)

* inspect CLI: dump the JSON for the image config to stdout

This CLI mimics `docker inspect`: it will print the OCI image config to
stdout as raw JSON. This can be used with `jq` or other tools to extract
useful metadata about an image.

Similar to `img pull`, `img inspect` only takes _one_ image (unlike
`docker inspect` which can take multiple and outputs an array). I felt
it was more important to act like img than it was to act like Docker.

* inspect: update help output to note incompatibility with docker inspect

commit.message:
Fix "prune" subcommand (#322)

The current implementation of `img prune` does not actually remove any
data. This changeset introduces an extra variadic argument to the
`Prune` call, producing behavior equivalent to `buildctl prune` invoked
without flags against a BuildKit daemon.

The issue and proposed fix become more clear with a look at the
underlying implementation, which loops over the variadic `PruneInfo`
arguments and runs a prune operation based on options specified in each
argument. With no arguments, it just attempts garbage collection on the
metadata store.

https://github.com/genuinetools/img/blob/d858ac71f93cc5084edd2ba2d425b90234cf2ead/vendor/github.com/moby/buildkit/cache/manager.go#L515-L520

commit.message:
Add fuse-overlayfs snapshot backend (#321)

This changeset introduces a `fuse-overlayfs` snapshot backend via
https://github.com/AkihiroSuda/containerd-fuse-overlayfs, providing
better performance and more efficient space usage than the `native`
backend when fuse-overlayfs is available.

The `auto` backend now prefers `fuse-overlayfs` to the `native` backend
when available. `overlayfs` is still preferred when Ubuntu kernel
patches are available.

The changeset also includes README updates, and dependency updates
resulting from the inclusion of the new module.

commit.message:
Add support for --cache-from (#279)

* Add support for --cache-from

This adds support for `docker build` style --cache-from. It achieves
this with two changes:

1. img will _always_ ask buildkit to export the build cache inline
2. img will pass through --cache-from arguments

* Update vendors

Use credential-helper creds, bypass prompt. (#276)

* Use credential-helper creds, bypass prompt.

This change respects the username and password we get back from the
credential helpers, enabling automated gcr and ecr creds helper
authentication for use in things like build pipelines.

Tested against `docker-credential-gcloud` and `docker-credential-ecr`.

* Cleanup diff newlines

* Remove unecessary sprintf that triggers linters

* Add change to reset pipeline
